('chunk_4c7e0a7b7eb8025237','file_8378b145fc1fad06fd','physics.md','Common Misconceptions Master List','1. **"Heavier objects fall faster than lighter ones."** In the absence of air resistance, all objects fall with the same acceleration (~10 m/s²); mass does not affect fall rate. A feather falls slowly only because of air resistance, not its lightness.
2. **"Mass and weight are the same."** Mass (kg) is the amount of matter and is constant; weight (N) is the gravitational force on that mass and changes with location.
3. **"A moving object needs a constant force to keep moving."** Force is required to *change* motion, not to maintain it; without friction, motion continues on its own.
4. **"If forces are balanced, the object must be at rest."** Balanced forces can also mean constant-velocity motion; zero net force means no change in motion, not necessarily no motion.
5. **"Precision and accuracy mean the same thing."** Precision is repeatability; accuracy is closeness to the true value — a measurement can be one without the other.
6. **"Doubling speed doubles kinetic energy."** Ek depends on v², so doubling speed quadruples kinetic energy.
7. **"Energy gets used up and disappears."** Energy is transformed, often into waste heat, but the total is always conserved.
8. **"Cutting a magnet gives a single pole."** Every piece keeps both a north and a south pole; no magnetic monopole exists.
9. **"All metals are magnetic."** Only iron, nickel, cobalt and their alloys are magnetic; copper, aluminium and gold are not.
10. **"A shooting star is a falling star."** It is a small meteoroid burning up in the atmosphere, not a star.
11. **"Moon phases are caused by Earth''s shadow."** Phases come from the Moon''s orbital position and which part of its sunlit side faces Earth; Earth''s shadow causes lunar eclipses only.
12. **"The Big Bang was an explosion in space."** Space itself expanded; there was no surrounding space to explode into.
13. **"A pushing force on a wall does work even if it doesn''t move."** No displacement means zero work done in physics.
14. **"Satellites stay up because there is no gravity in space."** Gravity provides the centripetal pull that keeps them orbiting; they are in continual free-fall around Earth.','{"common":1,"misconceptions":1,"master":1,"list":1,"heavier":1,"objects":2,"fall":4,"faster":1,"than":1,"lighter":1,"ones":1,"the":14,"absence":1,"air":2,"resistance":2,"all":2,"with":2,"same":3,"acceleration":1,"mass":4,"does":2,"not":6,"affect":1,"rate":1,"feather":1,"falls":1,"slowly":1,"only":3,"because":2,"its":3,"lightness":1,"and":9,"weight":2,"are":7,"amount":1,"matter":1,"constant":3,"gravitational":1,"force":5,"that":2,"changes":1,"location":1,"moving":2,"object":2,"needs":1,"keep":1,"required":1,"change":2,"motion":5,"maintain":1,"without":2,"friction":1,"continues":1,"own":1,"forces":2,"balanced":2,"must":1,"rest":1,"can":2,"also":1,"mean":2,"velocity":1,"zero":2,"net":1,"means":2,"necessarily":1,"precision":2,"accuracy":2,"thing":1,"repeatability":1,"closeness":1,"true":1,"value":1,"measurement":1,"one":1,"other":1,"doubling":2,"speed":2,"doubles":1,"kinetic":2,"energy":4,"depends":1,"quadruples":1,"gets":1,"used":1,"disappears":1,"transformed":1,"often":1,"into":2,"waste":1,"heat":1,"but":1,"total":1,"always":1,"conserved":1,"cutting":1,"magnet":1,"gives":1,"single":1,"pole":2,"every":1,"piece":1,"keeps":2,"both":1,"north":1,"south":1,"magnetic":3,"monopole":1,"exists":1,"metals":1,"iron":1,"nickel":1,"cobalt":1,"their":1,"alloys":1,"copper":1,"aluminium":1,"gold":1,"shooting":1,"star":3,"falling":1,"small":1,"meteoroid":1,"burning":1,"atmosphere":1,"moon":2,"phases":2,"caused":1,"earth":4,"shadow":2,"come":1,"from":1,"orbital":1,"position":1,"which":1,"part":1,"sunlit":1,"side":1,"faces":1,"causes":1,"lunar":1,"eclipses":1,"big":1,"bang":1,"was":2,"explosion":1,"space":4,"itself":1,"expanded":1,"there":2,"surrounding":1,"explode":1,"pushing":1,"wall":1,"work":2,"even":1,"doesn":1,"move":1,"displacement":1,"done":1,"physics":1,"satellites":1,"stay":1,"gravity":2,"provides":1,"