('chunk_bf66c0a9da38537db8','file_8378b145fc1fad06fd','physics.md','Cross-Subject Connections','- **Mathematics:** Motion graphs use gradient (slope) and area calculations; unit conversion, rearranging formulas (v = u + at, ρ = m/V), ratios and percentages (efficiency, mechanical advantage), and plotting/interpreting linear graphs all draw directly on maths skills. Scientific notation and significant figures link to number work.
- **Chemistry:** Density and states of matter connect to particle theory and material properties; energy resources and combustion of fossil fuels link to chemical reactions and chemical energy stored in bonds; the Big Bang and stellar life cycles explain the origin of chemical elements.
