('chunk_dca2a52ae2da527319','file_14c714e4dfcb7d1697','theatre.md','Subject Overview: Theatre in MYP Arts','Theatre belongs to the **MYP Arts** subject group. In the Arts, students act as **artists** — they investigate, develop skills, create/perform original work, and reflect on it. Theatre (drama) is a **performing art**: meaning is made live, in real time, through the body, voice, and space, in front of an audience.','{"subject":2,"overview":1,"theatre":3,"myp":2,"arts":3,"belongs":1,"the":3,"group":1,"students":1,"act":1,"artists":1,"they":1,"investigate":1,"develop":1,"skills":1,"create":1,"perform":1,"original":1,"work":1,"and":2,"reflect":1,"drama":1,"performing":1,"art":1,"meaning":1,"made":1,"live":1,"real":1,"time":1,"through":1,"body":1,"voice":1,"space":1,"front":1,"audience":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_a0a387752615c8ce5f','file_14c714e4dfcb7d1697','theatre.md','The Four MYP Arts Assessment Criteria','MYP Arts is assessed against four criteria, each out of **8 marks** (maximum level 8). Every criterion has strands described in level descriptors (1–2, 3–4, 5–6, 7–8).

| Criterion | Name | In Theatre, this means… |
|-----------|------|--------------------------|
| **A** | **Investigating** (Knowing & understanding) | Researching and understanding theatre forms, conventions, styles, practitioners and their contexts; using correct theatre vocabulary. |
| **B** | **Developing** | Developing skills and techniques; practising, exploring ideas, and planning a performance or creative intention. |
| **C** | **Creating / Performing** | Creating and/or performing theatre — realising a clear artistic intention on stage. |
| **D** | **Evaluating** | Reflecting on and evaluating one''s own and others'' work against the intention; appraising performances. |

> **Teacher note:** Different MYP Arts guides label Criterion A as "Investigating" (current framework) or "Knowing and understanding," and C as "Creating/Performing." Both refer to the same underlying skills. Assess with the descriptors your school has adopted for 2026–2027.','{"2026":1,"2027":1,"the":4,"four":2,"myp":3,"arts":3,"assessment":1,"criteria":2,"assessed":1,"against":2,"each":1,"out":1,"marks":1,"maximum":1,"level":2,"every":1,"criterion":3,"has":2,"strands":1,"described":1,"descriptors":2,"name":1,"theatre":4,"this":1,"means":1,"investigating":2,"knowing":2,"understanding":3,"researching":1,"and":9,"forms":1,"conventions":1,"styles":1,"practitioners":1,"their":1,"contexts":1,"using":1,"correct":1,"vocabulary":1,"developing":2,"skills":2,"techniques":1,"practising":1,"exploring":1,"ideas":1,"planning":1,"performance":1,"creative":1,"intention":3,"creating":3,"performing":3,"realising":1,"clear":1,"artistic":1,"stage":1,"evaluating":2,"reflecting":1,"one":1,"own":1,"others":1,"work":1,"appraising":1,"performances":1,"teacher":1,"note":1,"different":1,"guides":1,"label":1,"current":1,"framework":1,"both":1,"refer":1,"same":1,"underlying":1,"assess":1,"with":1,"your":1,"school":1,"adopted":1,"for":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_d5fac2874d9292885a','file_14c714e4dfcb7d1697','theatre.md','Arts Related Concepts (Theatre)','Related concepts are the "lenses" that sharpen inquiry in Theatre. Grade 7 draws on:

**role, character, narrative, genre, presentation, audience, structure, interpretation, expression, play, boundaries.**

| Related Concept | Quick meaning in Theatre |
|-----------------|--------------------------|
| **Role** | A part or function a performer takes on (e.g., narrator, villager, messenger). |
| **Character** | A specific fictional person with motives, background, and objectives (e.g., Antigone). |
| **Narrative** | The story being told and how events are ordered. |
| **Genre** | A category or type of theatre (tragedy, comedy, mime, musical). |
| **Presentation** | How work is shown to an audience — staging, delivery, visual choices. |
| **Audience** | The people watching; theatre is not complete without them. |
| **Structure** | How a piece is organised (scenes, acts, plot shape). |
| **Interpretation** | The meaning a performer or director brings to a text or idea. |
| **Expression** | Communicating emotion and meaning through voice, body, face. |
| **Play** | Both a dramatic text *and* the act of playful, imaginative exploration. |
| **Boundaries** | The limits performers push, test, or respect (of a stage, a role, a convention, an audience''s comfort). |','{"arts":1,"related":3,"concepts":2,"theatre":5,"are":2,"the":6,"lenses":1,"that":1,"sharpen":1,"inquiry":1,"grade":1,"draws":1,"role":3,"character":2,"narrative":2,"genre":2,"presentation":2,"audience":4,"structure":2,"interpretation":2,"expression":2,"play":2,"boundaries":2,"concept":1,"quick":1,"meaning":3,"part":1,"function":1,"performer":2,"takes":1,"narrator":1,"villager":1,"messenger":1,"specific":1,"fictional":1,"person":1,"with":1,"motives":1,"background":1,"and":4,"objectives":1,"antigone":1,"story":1,"being":1,"told":1,"how":3,"events":1,"ordered":1,"category":1,"type":1,"tragedy":1,"comedy":1,"mime":1,"musical":1,"work":1,"shown":1,"staging":1,"delivery":1,"visual":1,"choices":1,"people":1,"watching":1,"not":1,"complete":1,"without":1,"them":1,"piece":1,"organised":1,"scenes":1,"acts":1,"plot":1,"shape":1,"director":1,"brings":1,"text":2,"idea":1,"communicating":1,"emotion":1,"through":1,"voice":1,"body":1,"face":1,"both":1,"dramatic":1,"act":1,"playful":1,"imaginative":1,"exploration":1,"limits":1,"performers":1,"push":1,"test":1,"respect":1,"stage":1,"convention":1,"comfort":1}'::jsonb),
